
To return to Carnavaux, to my luggage, to Ivor Black carrying it, witha big show of travail, and muttering comedy stuff in some rudimentary role.

The sun had regained full control, when we entered a garden, separatedfrom the road by a stone wall and a row of cypresses. Emblematic irisessurrounded a green pondlet presided over by a bronze frog. From under acurly holm oak a graveled path ran between two orange trees. At one end ofthe lawn a eucalypt cast its striate shade across the canvas of a 